 :tx/rationale "AUTO-CONNECTION-HUB: Observations enter the store as isolated islands. The CRB system already tokenizes text and computes Jaccard similarity for duplicate detection. The SAME machinery, repurposed from preventing duplicates to PROPOSING CONNECTIONS, creates the graph structure FEGH needs. Implementation: connect_observations() runs after each braid observe. Tokenizes new observation, computes Jaccard against existing session observations. If J(Ti,Tj) > threshold, creates :connection/* datom with ADR-029 lifecycle attributes. NOT all-pairs (O(N^2)). Uses preferential attachment to top-log(N) hubs (observations with highest existing connection degree). This gives O(N*log(N)) scaling and power-law degree distribution. Hub observations are architectural insights that connect many details. Leaf observations are individual findings. The hub structure self-organizes. Connection weight = alpha1*jaccard(keywords) + alpha2*temporal_proximity + alpha3*cross_agent_bonus + alpha4*category_compatibility. Cross-agent connections are most valuable (knowledge synthesis no single agent achieved). Weights calibrate via hypothesis ledger: confirmed bridge from connection -> positive feedback, refuted -> negative. System learns which similarity signals predict genuine connections."
